Key Features & Learnings

    API Development:

        Created RESTful and dynamic APIs to manage application data.

        Implemented structured routing and controllers for maintainability.

    Middleware & Modular Architecture:

        Gained a deep understanding of middleware functions and modular design.

        Enhanced project scalability by organizing logic into reusable modules.

    Authentication & Authorization:

        Implemented user authentication using sessions or JWT.

        Developed role-based access control for secure user management.

        Integrated login and logout functionalities.

    Database Operations (CRUD):

        Performed Create, Read, Update, and Delete operations using MongoDB.

        Established relationships between data models for efficient data handling.

    File Handling:

        Implemented file upload functionality using Multer.

        Managed file storage and validation efficiently.